  "name": "NC-8 Negative Control — Clean Bounded Applicability Envelope (VAD Hemolysis CFD)",
  "description": "Clean UnitOfAssurance for CFD-based hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under VAD conditions. The ContextOfUse declares an explicit hasOperatingEnvelope (flow rate 3–6 L/min, rotational speed 2400–3600 RPM, hematocrit 35–45%) and hasApplicabilityConstraint (Newtonian blood rheology, rigid impeller assumption). Validation evidence densely covers this envelope at 15 operating points. All 13 credibility factors are assessed with achievedLevel >= requiredLevel. No weakeners are expected to fire; this package tests that W-ON-02 does not fire on a correctly bounded and densely validated COU.",
  "assuranceLevel": "High",
  "conformsToProfile_cou": "https://uofa.net/vocab#ProfileComplete",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 3,
